Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pour the cold @water{300%ml} for the rice into a medium #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

While the rice cooks, halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{30%g}.

In a large #bowl{}, combine the @Panko Breadcrumbs{10%g}, half the garlic, @Water{2%tbsp} and @salt{1/4%tsp} for the breadcrumb.

Add the @British Pork Mince{240%g} to the bowl and season with pepper, then mix together with your hands. Roll the mince into even-sized balls, 4 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the meatballs and peppers onto a large #baking tray{} and drizzle with @oil{1%tbsp}.

When your oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until the peppers are soft and the meatballs are browned on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The meatballs are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the remaining @Garlic Clove{1} and @Mexican Style Spice Mix{1%tsp} and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @Tomato Passata{1%250g} and @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Sugar{1/2%tsp} and @Water{100%ml} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer for ~{3-4%minutes}.

When the meatballs and peppers are cooked, stir them into the sauce and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes} more. Add a splash of water if it gets too thick.

When everything is ready, add the @Peas{120%g} to the rice and fluff it up using a #fork{}, then share between your #bowls{}.

Spoon the meatballs and spiced tomato sauce over the top of the rice. Finish with a sprinkle of cheese. Enjoy!